<bibRefCitation author="EGGER C" box="[750,901,1058,1080]" pageId="2" pageNumber="955" pagination="747 - 762" refId="ref4746" refString="SCHMID- EGGER C. (2003): New records of &quot; Sphecidae &quot; (Hymenoptera: Sphecidae &amp; Crabronidae) from Sicily (Italy) and Malta. - Linzer biologische Beitrage 35 (2): 747 - 762." type="journal article" year="2003">EGGER (2003)</bibRefCitation>
. Widely distributed in the Palaearctic region, most common in the northern territories, it becomes rare in the southern part. Its presence in 
<collectingCountry box="[517,593,1117,1139]" name="Algeria" pageId="2" pageNumber="955">Algeria</collectingCountry>
is doubtful (BITSCH &amp; LECLERCQ 1993). It is recorded from peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[413,462,1146,1168]" name="Italy" pageId="2" pageNumber="955">Italy</collectingCountry>
, as south as 
<collectingRegion box="[589,695,1146,1168]" country="Italy" name="Campania" pageId="2" pageNumber="955">Campania</collectingRegion>
.
